about.description:
Mono is a software platform designed to allow developers to easily create cross platform applications.
It is an open source implementation of Microsoft's .NET Framework based on the ECMA standards for C# and the Common Language Runtime.
about.summary: Mono is a software platform designed to allow developers to easily create cross platform applications.

name: mono
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "mono" %}
{% set version = "4.8.1.0" %}
{% set sha256 = "18cb38a670e51609c36c687ed90ad42cfedabeffd0a2dc5f7f0c46249eb8dbef" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.bz2
  url: http://download.mono-project.com/sources/{{ name }}/{{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.bz2
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  skip: True  # [not linux]

requirements:
  build:
    - toolchain
    - python
    - perl
    - automake
    - libtool
    - gettext
    - pkg-config
    - cmake

test:
  commands:
    - mono --version
    - mono --help

about:
  home: http://www.mono-project.com
  license: MIT
  license_file: LICENSE
  summary: |
    Mono is a software platform designed to allow developers to easily create cross platform applications.
  description: |
    Mono is a software platform designed to allow developers to easily create cross platform applications.
    It is an open source implementation of Microsoft's .NET Framework based on the ECMA standards for C# and the Common Language Runtime.
  doc_url: http://www.mono-project.com/docs/
  dev_url: https://github.com/mono/mono

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bgruening
